[{"location":"getting_started/#Installation","page":"Getting started","title":"Installation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"getting_started/","page":"Getting started","title":"Getting started","text":"DiracBilinears.jl can be installed with the Julia package manager:","category":"page"},{"location":"getting_started/","page":"Getting started","title":"Getting started","text":"julia -e 'import Pkg; Pkg.add(\"DiracBilinears\")'","category":"page"},{"location":"getting_started/#Usage","page":"Getting started","title":"Usage","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"getting_started/#Spatial-distribution","page":"Getting started","title":"Spatial distribution","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"getting_started/","page":"Getting started","title":"Getting started","text":"The following files are required:","category":"page"},{"location":"getting_started/","page":"Getting started","title":"Getting started","text":"seedname.scf.in\nseedname.nscf.in","category":"page"},{"location":"getting_started/","page":"Getting started","title":"Getting started","text":"Before evaluation of the bilinears, you need to perform DFT calculations by [Quantum ESPRESSO] to obtain the Bloch functions.","category":"page"},{"location":"getting_started/","page":"Getting started","title":"Getting started","text":"QE/bin/pw.x < seedname.scf.in > seedname.scf.out\nQE/bin/pw.x < seedname.nscf.in > seedname.nscf.out","category":"page"},{"location":"getting_started/","page":"Getting started","title":"Getting started","text":"[Quantum ESPRESSO]: https://www.quantum-espresso.org","category":"page"},{"location":"getting_started/","page":"Getting started","title":"Getting started","text":"To compute the spatial distribution of electron chirality, use the following commands:","category":"page"},{"location":"getting_started/","page":"Getting started","title":"Getting started","text":"using DiracBilinears\nτz = calc_density(calc=\"τz\", qedir=\"$outdir/seedname.save\")","category":"page"},{"location":"getting_started/","page":"Getting started","title":"Getting started","text":"Here, qedir should be set to the output directory from the Quantum ESPRESSO calculation, which contains the Bloch wave functions. The variable outdir corresponds to the directory specified in the nscf input file. You can select the physical quantity to calculate by specifying the calc option.  The available options are listed in the table below. |calc | Physical quantities | |:–-:|:–-:| |\"ρ\" (or \"rho\")|| electron density | |\"ms\"| magnetization | |\"j\"| current | |\"∇ms\" (or \"nablams\")|pseudoscalar| |\"τz\" (or \"tauz\")|electron chirality| |\"∇ρ\" (or \"nabla_rho\")| dradient part of polarization| |\"ps\"|spin-derived electric polarization|  ","category":"page"},{"location":"getting_started/","page":"Getting started","title":"Getting started","text":"You can generate the xsf file for [XCrySDen] plot after the calc_density() calculation:","category":"page"},{"location":"getting_started/","page":"Getting started","title":"Getting started","text":"write_density(τz; qedir=QEDIR, savefile=FILENAME)","category":"page"},{"location":"getting_started/","page":"Getting started","title":"Getting started","text":"The file extension of FILENAME must be set to \".xsf\".","category":"page"},{"location":"getting_started/","page":"Getting started","title":"Getting started","text":"[XCrySDen]: http://www.xcrysden.org/","category":"page"},{"location":"getting_started/#Wannier-matrix-element","page":"Getting started","title":"Wannier matrix element","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"getting_started/","page":"Getting started","title":"Getting started","text":"The following files are required:","category":"page"},{"location":"getting_started/","page":"Getting started","title":"Getting started","text":"seedname.scf.in\nseedname.pw2wan.in\nseedname.win.ref\nconf.toml","category":"page"},{"location":"getting_started/","page":"Getting started","title":"Getting started","text":"For the Wannier matrix elements, you first need to perform DFT calculations using [Quantum ESPRESSO] to obtain the Bloch functions.  You can do this by running:","category":"page"},{"location":"getting_started/","page":"Getting started","title":"Getting started","text":"QE/bin/pw.x < seedname.scf.in > seedname.scf.out","category":"page"},{"location":"getting_started/","page":"Getting started","title":"Getting started","text":"After completing the scf calculation, you can generate the Wannier functions using [Wannier90] and [wan2respack] 　(for more information, see the GitHub page of [wan2respack]).  First, run:","category":"page"},{"location":"getting_started/","page":"Getting started","title":"Getting started","text":"python Wan2respack/bin/wan2respack.py -pp conf.toml","category":"page"},{"location":"getting_started/","page":"Getting started","title":"Getting started","text":"This command will generate an input file seednamenscf_wannierin.  In this file, please replace calc=scf with calc=nscf. Next, calculate the Wannier functions by running:","category":"page"},{"location":"getting_started/","page":"Getting started","title":"Getting started","text":"QE/bin/pw.x < seedname.nscf_wannier.in > seedname.nscf_wannier.out\nWanier90/wannier90.x -pp seedname\nQE/bin/pw2wannier90.x < seedname.pw2wan.in > seedname.pw2wan.out\nWanier90/wannier90.x seedname\npython Wan2respack/bin/wan2respack.py conf.toml","category":"page"},{"location":"getting_started/","page":"Getting started","title":"Getting started","text":"[Quantum ESPRESSO]: https://www.quantum-espresso.org [Wannier90]: https://wannier.org [wan2respack]: https://github.com/respack-dev/wan2respack [RESPACK]: https://sites.google.com/view/kazuma7k6r","category":"page"},{"location":"getting_started/","page":"Getting started","title":"Getting started","text":"To compute the matrix elements, you need to specify the paths of two directories, \"dir-wfn-full\" (referred to as WFNDIR) and \"dir-wan\" (referred to as WANDIR).  These directories are generated by the [wan2respack] calculation.  To calculate the matrix elements of electron chirality, use the following commands:","category":"page"},{"location":"getting_started/","page":"Getting started","title":"Getting started","text":"using DiracBilinears\nrs, degen = calc_rgrid(mpmesh=(6,6,6))\nτz, rs = calc_wannier_matrix(calc=\"τz\", rgrid=rs, wfndir=WFNDIR, wandir=WANDIR)","category":"page"},{"location":"getting_started/","page":"Getting started","title":"Getting started","text":"Please set the Monkhorst-Pack mesh size for the scf calculation in mpmesh.  You can choose the calc option from the table shown below. |calc | Physical quantities | |:–-:|:–-:| |\"ρ\" (or \"rho\")| electron density | |\"ms\"| magnetization | |\"j\"| current | |\"τz\" (or \"tau_z\", \"chirality\")|electron chirality| |\"ps\"|spin-derived electric polarization| ","category":"page"},{"location":"getting_started/","page":"Getting started","title":"Getting started","text":"The Wannier matrix elements can be saved to a text file using the following command:","category":"page"},{"location":"getting_started/","page":"Getting started","title":"Getting started","text":"write_wannier_matrix(τz, rs; savefile=FILENAME)","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = DiracBilinears","category":"page"},{"location":"#DiracBilinears","page":"Home","title":"DiracBilinears","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"This document provides usage for DiracBilinears.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"This package provides tools for computing microscopic physical quantities in relativistic quantum theory called Dirac bilinears, which are the fundamental 16 independent quantities derived from the Dirac field. By connecting to the external first-principles calculation package Quantum ESPRESSO, Wannier90, and wan2respack, it can evaluate ","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"spatial distributions of the bilinears\nWannier matrix elements of the bilinears","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Modules = [DiracBilinears]","category":"page"}]
